public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        double x = Math.log10(n) / Math.log10(3);

        return Math.abs(x - Math.round(x)) < 1e-10;
    }
}
```

This solution first checks if the number is less than or equal to zero, in which case it returns `false` because a power of three must be greater than zero.

Then, it calculates the logarithm base 3 of the number. If the result is an integer, it means the number is a power of three.

To check if the result is an integer, the solution uses the fact that the absolute difference between the number and its rounded value should be very close to zero (less than 1e-10) if the number is an integer.

This solution does not use loops or recursion.

